    "refcode_long": "The Adventist Home, p. 402.4 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "It is not safe for us to linger to contemplate the advantages to be reaped through yielding to Satan&apos;s suggestions. Sin means dishonor and disaster to every soul that indulges in it; but it is blinding and deceiving in its nature, and it will entice us with flattering presentations. <span class=\"page-break\" data-page=\"403\"></span> If we venture on Satan&apos;s ground, we have no assurance of protection from his power. So far as in us lies, we should close every avenue by which the tempter may find access to us.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">9<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"MB 118.1\" data-link=\"150.609\">Thoughts From the Mount of Blessing, 118</span>.</span></a></sup>",
