    "refcode_3": "1",
    "refcode_4": "",
    "refcode_short": "AH 404.1",
    "refcode_long": "The Adventist Home, p. 404.1 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Those who would have that wisdom which is from God must become fools in the sinful knowledge of this age, in order to be wise. They should shut their eyes, that they may see and learn no evil. They should close their ears, lest they hear that which is evil and obtain that knowledge which would stain their purity of thoughts and acts. And they should guard their tongues, lest they utter corrupt communications and guile be found in their mouths.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">14<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"SA 76.1\" data-link=\"4.100\">A Solemn Appeal, 76</span>.</span></a></sup>",
