    "refcode_long": "The Adventist Home, p. 405.2 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "While we should be keenly alive to our exposure to the assaults of unseen and invisible foes, we are to be sure that they cannot harm us without gaining our consent.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">17<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"RH 7-19-1887\" data-link=\"821.8338\">The Review and Herald, July 19, 1887</span>.</span></a></sup>",
